From 46b807a06b53a6966279c1df5d820b87e4a30727 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@local>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 05:10:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] KVM: Diagnostic skip accessed mark on PFN release

Bad-page reports during the old-ABI TDX runs consistently trip
PAGE_FLAGS_CHECK_AT_PREP with PG_referenced left on a free page, and the stack
passes through KVM's hva_to_pfn()/kvm_faultin_pfn() path.

As a narrow diagnostic, stop marking pages accessed from KVM's clean PFN
release helper. This should not change TDX or CoFunc semantics; it only avoids
touching the page's reclaim/accessed state while we test whether KVM's release
path is leaving PG_referenced behind on pages that later return to the buddy
allocator.
---
 virt/kvm/kvm_main.c | 8 ++++++--
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/virt/kvm/kvm_main.c
+++ b/virt/kvm/kvm_main.c
@@ -3097,8 +3097,12 @@ static void kvm_set_page_dirty(struct page *page)
 
 static void kvm_set_page_accessed(struct page *page)
 {
-	if (kvm_is_ad_tracked_page(page))
-		mark_page_accessed(page);
+	/*
+	 * Diagnostic for old-ABI TDX bad-page reports: avoid leaving
+	 * PG_referenced on pages released through KVM's PFN path.
+	 */
+	if (kvm_is_ad_tracked_page(page))
+		return;
 }
 
 void kvm_release_page_clean(struct page *page)
